== English ==
{{wikipedia}}
=== Etymology ===
From Italian ''[[soprano#Italian|soprano]]'', from Latin ''[[sopranus]]'', adjective form from preposition ''[[super#Latin|super]]'' (above).
=== Pronunciation ===
*{{audio|en-us-soprano.ogg|Audio (US)}}
=== Noun ===
'''soprano'' (''plural: '''[[sopranos]]''' or, uncommonly, '''[[soprani]]''''')
#Musical part or section higher in pitch than [[alto]] and other sections.
#Person or [[instrument]] that performs the soprano part. 
